						               													<description>From the box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gender Gap 2 is a game that tests both adult men and adult women on their ability to predict how other players really think about present day issues and situations. The questions are designed to be both topical and likely controversial, with the hope that it will create exciting discussion among the players regarding moral, ethical, relationship, parental and lifestyle topics. Gender Gap 2 deals with situations that are top of mind but sometimes never discussed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Brief description:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take it in turn to act as a reader, reading aloud a statement relating to gender roles (i.e. &amp;quot;European men are more secure in their masculinity than North American men&amp;quot;). The reader than picks a rating from 1 (strongly disagree) to 7 (strongly agree) and everyone else secretly tries to guess the readers choice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The choice and all guesses are revealed simultaneously. Correct guessers roll the dice to move forward, everyone else moves back a number of spaces equal to the difference between the guess and the actual answer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
